Installation of GeneMark-HM piepline

To install, copy the content of "bin" folder to desired location.

Software was tested under Perl 5.10.

Perl scripts are configure as "/usr/bin/perl".
The following CPAN Perl modules are required:
* Parallel::ForkManager

NCBI "blastn" executable is expected in shell PATH. 
Alternatively, path to “blastn” can be set directly in "gm_hm.pl" script by modifying the line 
    my $blastn = "blastn";

Download and install database of model files and databse of pan-genome sequences

cd bin
wget http://geneprobe.net/genemark_hm/refmod.tar
tar xf refmod.tar

mkdir refdb
cd refdb
wget http://geneprobe.net/genemark_hm/pan.fasta
makeblastdb -in pan.fasta  -parse_seqids -dbtype nucl  -out pan -title pan

Pipeline is ready for execution.
